===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|grc|ἐσωτερικός|t=belonging to an inner circle}}, from {{m|grc|ἐσωτέρω|t=further inside}}, comparative of {{m|grc|ἔσω|t=within}}, from {{m|grc|ἐς}}, {{m|grc|εἰς|t=into}} (''esoteric'' originally referred to the secret teachings of Greek philosophers, versus public or [[exoteric]] ones).

